Date: Tue, 24 Mar 1998 09:45:19 -0800
From: Tom Pringle <tom@cyber-dyne.com>
Source: Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy <BSE-L@RZ.UNI-KARLSRUHE.DE>

Below is the full text of the 1881 case of 'scrapie in a cow' of 8 years
age from an 1883 French medical veterinary journal article. It has no list
of citations at the end as was typical for scientific articles until after
WWI.
I also intercalated a thoroughly mangled translation. Please feel free to
correct this if you are able. Dr. Elisabeth Claman, a specialist in late
nineteenth century French literature at UO and a professional translator
with 30 years experience, has agreed to look over our best effort for
nuances. I will post both French and (ongoing version ) English full texts
at http://www.mad-cow.org/boeuf.html
Did this cow in fact exhibit symptoms of a bovine TSE? The quality of
supporting evidence is open for discussion. Please let us not fault the
veterinarian for not doing a western blot, electron microscopy, or prion
gene sequencing.
If yes, did it have an origin in scrapie? One scenario is that the cow was
exposed to scrapie in co-pastured sheep, i.e., horizontal transmission.
This may have occurred earlier in the herd with subsequent cow-to-cow
transmission so that the cow of the article was not the primary passage.
This might be called scrapie-BSE or scrapie-in-a-cow to indicate origin,
keeping in mind that the cow prion causes the problem, not the long-gone
sheep prion of different sequence. It is not scrapie any more, scrapie is
a disease only sheep can get.
A second scenario is a validation of the Gibbs Principle, familial bovine
TSE, that is, the cow had a familial CJD-type mutation in its prion gene as
expected from the one per million background mutational rate. Other
variants are somatic mutation bovine TSE or sporadic bovine TSE. These
might be called familial BSE or sporadic BSE, keeping in mind that:
Neither scenario makes the ailment of this cow equivalent to either modern
day UK BSE or Stetsonville BSE. This would be an unlikely coincidence
because of the many possible strain types. Both scenarios are supportive,
but certainly not proof, of the concept that some sporadic CJD in humans
might long have had a dietary origin.
...........
Un cas de tremblante sur un boeuf.
Par M. Sarraet, veterinaire a Carbone (Haute-Garonne).
Revue médicale vétérinaire, 7, 310-312 1883
A case of scrapie in a cow
By M. Serraet, veterinary at Carbone in Haute-Garonne, France
Medical Veterinary Review 7: 310-312 1883

La tremblante est consideree comme une maladie exclusive du mouton; le fait
suivant prouve que cette nevrose peur aussi attaquer les animaux de
l'espece bovine.
-- Scrapie is considered as an illness exclusively of sheep; the facts
below prove that this nervous condition may also attack animals of the
bovine species.
Le sujet sur lequel il m'a ete done de faire cette observation interessante
est un boeuf de race gasconne sous poil gris clair, age de 8 ans,
apparienant a M. Menville, fermier a Rieux.
-- The subject on which these interesting observations were made is a cow
of the Gasconne breed with clear gray hide, 8 years of age, belonging to M.
Menville, a farmer in Rieux, France.
Dans les dernier jours du mois de novembre 1881, cet animal fut an proie a
un prurit si intense de la base de la queue, qu'il se grattait contre tous
les objets qui se trouvaient a sa portee. A l'ecurie, il se frottait avec
une veritable fureur contre la stalle ou contre son voisin, a la prairie,
contre tous le arbres qu'il peavait rencontrer; attele, contre la partie
anterieure de la charrette ou, s'il ne pouvait y atteindere, il se
contournait pour se froiter contre le timon.
-- In the last days of the month of November 1881, this animal began to
experience an intense inching at the base of the neck, which it scratched
against all the objects that it found in its stall. In the barn, it rubbed
with a veritable furor against the stall or against its restraint; in the
pasture, against all the trees that it could find; shackled, against the
front part of the post where, if it could not reach, it contorted itself to
scratch against the stanchion.
Cette violente demangeaison avait cause une excoriation large et profonde
et, par moment, une hemorrhagie assez abondante de la base de la queue.
-- This violent scratching caused a large and deep excoriation and, after
time, substantial bleeding at the base of the neck.
Du reste, a part ce prurit incommode qui torturait sans cess l'animal et un
certain degre d'amaigrissement facile a expliquer, il ne presenait pas
d'autre symptome digne d'etre note.
-- After this, beyond the dehabilitating pruritis which tormented this
animal without cessation and a certain degree of easily explained
accompanying conditions, it did not present other symptoms worthy of note.
Il en fut ainsi jusqu'au 13 decembre. Le matin de ce jour, le prurit
toujour tres vif semblait avoir reagi sur le'etat general du boeuf en
question. L'appetit avai diminue, la rumination etait lente et rare. Il
tenait la tete tres bass ou enfoncee dans la mangeoire; dans cette
position, il appuyait parfois le front contre le mur et poussait al la
facon d'un cheval atteint du vertige. Il ne sortait de cet etat comateux
que pour frotter sa queue avec frenesie.
-- This went on until 13 Dec 1881. In the morning of this day, the itching
lively as ever appeared to have affected the general state of the cow in
question. The appetite was diminished, and chewing of cud (rumination) was
slow and seldom. It held its head very low and depressed in the manger; in
this position, it positioned itself at the front against the wall and had
the general appearance of a dizzy horse. It did not leave this comatose
state while it scratched its neck with frenzy.
En meme temps que ces symptomes setaient manifestes du cote de l'encephale,
une paralysie evidente commencait a envahir le train posterieur; dans les
mouvement auxquels il se livrait pour satisfaire le prurit qui le devoinit
pour ainse dire, l'animal tombait de Parriere-train et ce n'etait qu'avec
peine qu'il parvenait a se relever. La demarch etait mal assuree; les
members posterieurs etaient vacillants et trainaient sur le sol.
--At the same time that these symptoms manifested themselves on the side of
the head, an obvious paralysis began to effect the posterior gait; with the
movement of which it used to satisfy the itching which consumed it, to put
another way, the animal fell into the Parriere-gait and it was only with
difficulty that it could get up. The sequal was assuredly bad; the
posterior limbs were flailing about and
pointed skyward.
Le 16, tous ces symptomes se sont aggraves; le'appetit et la rumination son
entierement suspendus; la paralysie a fait des progres remarquables;
l'animal peut a peine se tenir sur ses jambes. Enon, vers les trois heures
du soir; il tombe pour ne plus se relever. Il est etendu sur le cote droit
en decubitus lateral; dans cette situation, l'oeil est piroettant dans
l'orbite, la pupille fortement dilatee et la conjonctive tres injectee; la
panse est tres meteorisee par suite l'inrumination et de la position du
malade. La respiration et tres lente; sans quelques leger movement
convulsifs des quatre membres et une certain conservation de la sensibilite
generale, l'animal semblerait mort.
--By 16 Dec 1881, all of these symptoms had become aggravated; the appetite
and rumination entirely suspended; the paralysis remarkably progressed; the
animal could only with difficulty pull itself with its limbs. Then, in the
third hour of the evening, it fell, never to rise again. A lateral
decubitus was found on the right side; in this situation, the eye is
piroetting within the orbit, the pupil strongly dilated and the conjunctiva
very injected; the rumen strongly dilated in consequence of ceased
rumination and the position of the injurty. Respiration is very slow,
except for some slow convulsive movements of the four limbs and a general
conservation of awareness, the animal appears dead.
Diagnostic. -- Au debut, alors que le prurit existai seul, il etait aise de
prendre cette affection pour un simple prurigo. Mais lorsqu'est survnue la
complication de phenomenes cerbraux et surtout la paralysie, un
rapprocement s'est fait instinctivement dans mon esprit entre la maladie
dont je viens de faire la symptomatologie et la tremblante du mouton.
J'ai analyse comparativement ces deux affections et j'ai trouve entre elles
des rapports si intimes, que je n'hesite pas a affirmer que ja'ai eu
affaire a la forme pruriingeuse de la tremblante.
-- Diagnostics: In the beginning, when there was just the itching, the
affliction seemed to just be a simple puritis. But after factoring in the
complication of the cerebral phenomena and above all the paralysis, an
instinctive convergence in my mind occured with the malady I have come
across in the symptomatology and the scrapie of sheep.
-- I made a comparative analysis of the two afflictions and I found such a
close agreement between them, that I wouldn't hesitate to affirm that is a
matter of an itching form of scrapie.
Pronostic. -- La tremblante, chez le mouton, consitutue une maladie grave,
puisqu'elle guerit rarement. D'apres le cas que j'ai eu la bonne fortune
d'observer, elle semblerait encore plus grave sur le boeuf; elle
parcourrait plus rapidement ses periodes et se terminerait d'une facon
aussie malheureuse.
-- Prognostics: Scrapie, in sheep, is a serious malady which one encounters
rarely. After this case which I had the good fortune to observe, scrapie
seems even more grave in cattle; it runs its course more rapidly and
terminates in even worse a fashion.
Dal l'espece, l'etat m'a paru desesepre; aussi j'ai cur toute medication
inutile et j'ai conseille au proprietaire l'abatage du boeuf qui a ete
vendu pour la basse boucherie.
-- In this species, the condition appears to me hopeless; also, I think all
medication without utility and I would advise the manager of a cattle
abattoir that it should be sold only at the low grade butcher's shop.
--
Tom Pringle
e-mail: tom@cyber-dyne.com
[For those interested in the "possible" origins of BSE, the following French
paper may have interest. However, caveat lector. - Mod.MHJ
Sarraet M., 1883. Un cas de tremblante sur un boeuf. Revue medicale
veterinaire, 7, 310-312. (A case of scrapie in beef - Veterinary medical
review)
